{{Distinguish|性向认同|性取向|社会性别}}
'''性別認同'''（{{lang-en|Gender identity}}）是一个人对自己[[社會性別|性別]]的个人感觉。<ref name="MorrowMessinger">''Sexual Orientation and Gender Expression in Social Work Practice'', edited by Deana F. Morrow and Lori Messinger (2006, {{ISBN|0231501862}}), p. 8: "Gender identity refers to an individual's personal sense of identity as masculine or feminine, or some combination thereof."</ref>性别认同可以与一个人出生时的[[指定性别|指定性别]]相关，也可以与之不同。<ref>{{cite web|title=Sexual Orientation and Gender Identity Definitions|url=http://www.hrc.org/resources/sexual-orientation-and-gender-identity-terminology-and-definitions|last=Campaign|first=Human Rights|access-date=2018-05-29|archive-date=2015-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151125033133/http://www.hrc.org/resources/sexual-orientation-and-gender-identity-terminology-and-definitions|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[性別表現|性別表現]]通常反映一个人的性别认同，但情况并非总是如此。<ref name="Summers">{{cite book|last1=Summers|first1=Randal W.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5nF1DQAAQBAJ&pg=PA232|title=Social Psychology: How Other People Influence Our Thoughts and Actions [2 volumes]|date=2016|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=9781610695923|page=232}}</ref><ref name="APA2015">{{cite journal|title=Guidelines for Psychological Practice With Transgender and Gender Nonconforming People|url=http://www.apa.org/practice/guidelines/transgender.pdf|date=December 2015|journal=American Psychologist|issue=9|doi=10.1037/a0039906|volume=70|page=861|pmid=26653312|author1=American Psychological Association|access-date=2020-08-22|archive-date=2019-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190929202948/https://www.apa.org/practice/guidelines/transgender.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>虽然一个人可能会表現出与特定[[性别角色|性别角色]]相一致的行为、态度和外貌，但这种表現不一定反映出他们的性别认同。性别认同这个词最初是由Robert Jesse Stoller在1964年发明的。<ref>{{cite journal|title=The Hermaphroditic Identity of Hermaphrodites|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-nervous-and-mental-disease_1964-11_139_5/page/453|first1=ROBERT J.|date=November 1964|journal=The Journal of Nervous and Mental Disease|issue=5|doi=10.1097/00005053-196411000-00005|volume=139|pages=453–457|pmid=14227492|last1=STOLLER}}</ref>

所有社会都有一套性别范畴，可以作為一個人在其他相聯繫的社會成員中形成[[身份認同|身份認同]]的基礎。<ref>V. M. Moghadam, ''Patriarchy and the politics of gender in modernising societies'', in ''International Sociology'', 1992: "All societies have gender systems."</ref>在大多數社會中，[[指定性別|指定性別]]中的[[男性特質|男性特質]]和[[女性特質|女性特質]]之間存在基本的分歧，<ref name="Carlson">{{citation|last1=Carlson|pages=[https://archive.org/details/psychologyscienc0004unse/page/140 140–41]|postscript=.|ref=harv|edition=4th|isbn=978-0205645244|year=2009|location=Toronto, Canada|publisher=Pearson|title=Psychology: the science of behaviour|first1=Neil R.|editor-first2=C. Donald|editor-last2=Heth|editor-first1=Neil R.|editor-last1=Carlson|contribution=Sensation|first2=C. Donald|last2=Heth|url=https://archive.org/details/psychologyscienc0004unse/page/140}}</ref>这是大多数人坚持的[[性别二元論|性别二元論]]，其中包括對性別（[[生物性別|生物性別]]、性別認同和[[性別表現|性別表現]]）所有方面的[[男性特质|男性特质]]和[[女性特质|女性特质]]的期望。<ref>Jack David Eller, ''Culture and Diversity in the United States'' (2015, {{ISBN|1317575784}}), p. 137: "most Western societies, including the United States, traditionally operate with a binary notion of sex/gender"</ref>有些人並不認同（或不完全認同）基於[[生物性別|生物性別]]的[[性別指定|性別指定]]，<ref>For example, "transvestites [who do not identify with the dress assigned to their sex] existed in almost all societies." (G. O. MacKenzie, ''Transgender Nation'' (1994, {{ISBN|0879725966}}), p. 43.) "There are records of males and females crossing over throughout history and in virtually every culture. It is simply a naturally occurring part of all societies." (Charles Zastrow, ''Introduction to Social Work and Social Welfare: Empowering People'' (2013, {{ISBN|128554580X}}), p. 234, quoting the North Alabama Gender Center.)</ref>例如一些人是[[跨性別|跨性別]]，[[性別酷兒|性別酷兒]]者或[[非二元性別|非二元性別]]人群。有一些社會有[[第三性別|第三性別]]分類。

性别认同通常在三岁时形成。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Bukatko|first1=Danuta|last2=Daehler|first2=Marvin W.|title=Child Development: A Thematic Approach|date=2004|publisher=Houghton Mifflin|isbn=978-0-618-33338-7|page=[https://archive.org/details/childdevelopment0000buka/page/495 495]|url=https://archive.org/details/childdevelopment0000buka|url-access=registration|language=en}}</ref><ref name="IntBehavSciMed">{{cite book|last1=Hine|first5=R. B.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0UYyBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA106|page=106|isbn=978-1-4612-5452-2|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|date=2012|title=Introduction to Behavioral Science in Medicine|last5=Williams|first1=F. R.|first4=R. J. Jr|last4=Thompson|first3=G. L.|last3=Maddox|first2=R. C.|last2=Carson|language=en|access-date=2020-08-22|archive-date=2020-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200701002454/https://books.google.com/books?id=0UYyBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA106|dead-url=no}}</ref>三岁以后，改变是非常困难的，<ref name=IntBehavSciMed/>並嘗試改變性別認同会导致[[性别不安|性别不安]]。<ref name="Boles101102">Boles, 2013. Pages 101-102.</ref>生物和社會因素都被認為影響性別認同的形成。

==形成年齡==
关于性别认同的形成方式和时间有好几种理论，研究这一主題很困难，因为儿童缺乏语言能力，需要研究人员从间接证据中作出假设。<ref name="Boles101102" />[[約翰·曼尼|約翰·曼尼]]認爲孩子們可能早在年齡18個月到兩歲之間就已經意識到性別，並且認爲性別具有一定的意義。[[勞倫斯·柯爾伯格|勞倫斯·柯爾伯格]]认为，性别认同要到3岁才能形成。<ref name="Boles101102"/>專家普遍認為，核心性别认同在三岁就已经牢牢地形成了。<ref name="Boles101102"/><ref>A few authorities say it forms between ages 3–4 rather than precisely at age 3, e.g. George J. Bryjak and Michael P. Soraka, ''Sociology: Cultural Diversity in a Changing World'' (ed. Karen Hanson), Allyn & Bacon, 1997; 209–45</ref>在三歲時，儿童可以坚定地表明自己的性别，<ref name="Boles101102"/><ref name="Newmann">{{cite book|last=Newmann|first=Barbara|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oTY_7osGmqUC|title=Development Through Life: A Psychosocial Approach|date=2012-12-20|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=978-1111344665|page=243|access-date=2018-08-04|archive-date=2021-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203231201/https://books.google.com/books?id=oTY_7osGmqUC|dead-url=no}}</ref>並倾向于选择适合他們性别的活动和玩具<ref name="Boles101102"/>（如女孩的娃娃和繪畫，男孩的工具和粗糙的住房），<ref>Christopher Bates Doob, ''Social Inequality and Social Stratification in US Society''</ref>尽管他们尚未完全理解性别的含义。<ref name="Newmann"/>三歲以後，核心的性別認同改變是非常困難的，<ref name="Kleeman">J. A. Kleeman, ''The establishment of core gender identity in normal girls. I.(a) Introduction;(b) Development of the ego capacity to differentiate'', in the ''Archives of Sexual Behavior'', 1971: "Though gender identity formation continues into young adulthood and core gender identity establishment extends into the fourth year and possibly longer, core gender identity is fairly firmly formed by age 3[.]"</ref>並且嘗試改變性別認同会导致[[性別不安|性別不安]]。<ref name="Boles101102"/><ref>E. Coleman, ''Developmental stages of the coming out process'', in ''Journal of homosexuality'', 1982: "Core gender and sex-role identities are well-formed by the age of 3 (Money & Ehrhardt, 1972). This is believed because attempts to reassign gender identity after age 3 result in further gender dysphoria."</ref>性別認同的固化持續到四歲<ref name="Kleeman" />至六歲<ref name="Boles101102"/><ref>Stein MT, Zucker KJ, Dixon SD. December, 1997. "Gender Identity", ''The Nurse Practitioner''. Vo. 22, No. 12, p. 104</ref>，並持續到青春期。<ref name="Kleeman"/>

Martin和Ruble将这一发展过程概念化为三个阶段：（1）作為幼兒和學齡前兒童，兒童學習既定的性別社會化特徵。（2）年齡在5-7歲左右，性別認同得到鞏固並變得僵化。（3）在這種「僵化高峰」之後，流動性回歸，社會定義的[[性別角色|性別角色]]的認知有所緩和些。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Children's Search for Gender Cues Cognitive Perspectives on Gender Development|first1=C.|last2=Ruble|first2=D.|journal=Current Directions in Psychological Science|issue=2|doi=10.1111/j.0963-7214.2004.00276.x|year=2004|volume=13|pages=67–70|last1=Martin|s2cid=33579865}}</ref>Barbara Newmann將其分為四個部分：（1）理解性別概念。（2）學習性別角色標準和刻板印象。（3）與父母一起認同。（4）形成性別偏好。<ref name="Newmann" />

据联合国的机构称，有关全方位性教育的讨论提高了人们对性别和性别认同等主题的认识。<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0026/002607/260770e.pdf|title=International technical guidance on sexuality education: An evidence-informed approach|publisher=UNESCO|year=2018|isbn=978-92-3-100259-5|location=Paris|page=18|access-date=2018-08-04|archive-date=2018-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113072101/http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0026/002607/260770e.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 影響形成的因素 ==
===先天與後天===
{{Main article|先天與後天}}

虽然对性別認同的形成尚未完全理解，但已提出許多因素被認爲影響其發展。特别是，社會化（環境因素）與先天（生物）因素決定性別認同的程度是心理學中持續存在的爭論，被稱為「先天與後天」。這兩個因素都被認為對性別認同起了影響。影響個體性別認同的生物因素包括產前和產後激素水平。<ref name="ZhongNan">''Effects of male sex hormones on gender identity, sexual behavior, and cognitive function'', ''Zhong Nan Da Xue Xue Bao, Yi Xue Ban'' (''Journal of Central South University, Medical Sciences''), April 2006, 31(2):149-61</ref>雖然基因的構成也會影響性別認同，<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The concept of gender identity disorder in childhood and adolescence after 39 years|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-sex-and-marital-therapy_fall-1994_20_3/page/163|first1=John|authorlink=John Money|journal=Journal of Sex and Marital Therapy|issue=3|doi=10.1080/00926239408403428|year=1994|volume=20|pages=163–77|pmid=7996589|last1=Money}}</ref>但它並不會對其產生一成不变的影響。<ref>Susan Golombok, Robyn Fivush, ''Gender Development'' (1994, {{ISBN|0521408628}}), p. 44: "When assigned and raised as boys, these genetic girls adopt a male gender identity and role, showing that a Y chromosome is not necessary for gender development to proceed in a male direction."</ref>

可能影響性別認同的社會因素包括家庭、權威人物、大眾媒體以及其他在儿童生活中有影响力的人所传达對性别角色观念。<ref name="Henslin">{{cite book|last=Henslin|first=James M.|title=Essentials of Sociology|publisher=Taylor & Francis|year=2001|isbn=978-0-536-94185-5|pages=65–67, 240}}</ref>當孩子由某個堅持嚴格性別角色的人士撫養時，他們更有可能以相同的方式行事，將他們的性別認同與相應的刻板印象的性別模式相匹配。<ref>{{cite web|title=Factors Influencing Gender Identity|url=https://www.mentalhelp.net/articles/factors-influencing-gender-identity/|access-date=2018-08-06|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305080254/https://www.mentalhelp.net/articles/factors-influencing-gender-identity/|dead-url=no}}</ref>語言也發揮著作用，兒童在學習語言的同時，學會區別[[男性化|男性化]]和[[女性化|女性化]]特徵，並下意識地將自己的行為調整為這些預定的角色。<ref>Williams, Michael, "Cultural Identity, Language Identity, Gender Identity", "The English Academy of South Africa", 2011</ref>[[社會學習理論|社會學習理論]]認為，儿童通过观察和模仿与性别相关的行为来进一步发展他们的性别认同，然後因為這種行為受到獎勵或懲罰，<ref name="myers">Myers, David G. (2008). ''Psychology''. New York: Worth.</ref>因此藉由模仿和追隨周圍人們的性別模式來塑造人格。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Cognitive theories of early gender development|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_psychological-bulletin_2002-11_128_6/page/903|first1=C. L.|last2=Ruble|first2=D. N.|journal=Psychological Bulletin|issue=6|doi=10.1037/0033-2909.128.6.903|year=2002|volume=128|pages=903–06|pmid=12405137|last3=Szkrybalo|first3=J.|last1=Martin|citeseerx=10.1.1.460.3216}}</ref>

在早期的性别认同研究中[[約翰·曼尼|約翰·曼尼]]起了重要的作用，儘管他使用了「[[性別角色|性別角色]]」一詞，而不是性別認同。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Zucker|first1=Kenneth J.|url=https://www.springer.com/gp/book/9781402043130|title=Ethics and Intersex|date=2006|publisher=Springer Netherlands|isbn=978-1-4020-4313-0|editor1-last=Sytsma|editor1-first=Sharon E.|page=167|language=en|access-date=2020-08-23|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308133040/https://www.springer.com/gp/book/9781402043130|dead-url=no}}</ref>他不同意前學派的观点，即性别認同完全由生物因素决定。他辩称，婴儿出生时是一張白紙，父母可以决定婴儿的性别。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=NOVA {{!}} Transcripts {{!}} Sex: Unknown {{!}} PBS|url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/transcripts/2813gender.html|access-date=2018-12-07|website=www.pbs.org|archive-date=2011-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111011043248/http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/transcripts/2813gender.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>在曼尼看来，如果父母有信心把自己的孩子当作异性抚养，则该孩子会相信自己出生就是那個性別，并採取相對應的行為舉止。<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|last=Colapinto|first=John|title=As nature made him : the boy who was raised as a girl|url=https://archive.org/details/asnaturemadehimb0000cola_p0v2|date=2006|publisher=HarperCollins|isbn=978-0061120565|edition=1st Harper Perennial|location=New York|oclc=71012749|author-link=John Colapinto}}</ref>曼尼相信后天的培养可以凌驾于先天之上。<ref name=":1" />

先天與後天爭論中一個眾所周知的例子是[[大衛·利馬|大衛·利馬]]，也就是所謂的「約翰/瓊案例」。利馬在嬰兒時，經歷了一次錯誤的閹割，失去了他的男性生殖器。心理學家[[約翰·曼尼|約翰·曼尼]]說服利馬的父母將他當作女孩撫養。利馬長大成女孩，穿著女孩衣服，周圍都是女孩玩具，但感覺自己不像女孩。在他13歲時試圖自殺後，利馬被告知他出生時具有男性生殖器，並進行了重建手術。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Nolen-Hoeksema|title=Abnormal Psychology|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781308211503|date=2014|publisher=McGraw-Hill|isbn=978-1308211503|edition=6|page=[https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781308211503/page/368 368]}}<!--|accessdate=5 December 2014--></ref>這違背了曼尼的假設，即人類的性別認同或性取向與生物因素無關。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Cognitive Theories of Early Gender Development|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_psychological-bulletin_2002-11_128_6/page/903|last=Martin|first=Carol|journal=Psychological Bulletin|issue=6|doi=10.1037/0033-2909.128.6.903|year=2002|volume=128|pages=903–13|pmid=12405137|author3=Joel Szkrybalo|author2=Diane Ruble|citeseerx=10.1.1.460.3216}}</ref>

=== 生物因素 ===
一些產前生物因素，包括基因和激素，可能會影響性別認同。<ref name="ZhongNan"/><ref name="Ghosh">{{cite web|title=Gender Identity|url=http://emedicine.medscape.com/article/917990-overview|accessdate=October 29, 2012|last=Ghosh|first=Shuvo|publisher=MedScape|archive-date=2021-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210306211817/https://emedicine.medscape.com/article/917990-overview|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 雙性人 ====
{{main article|雙性人}}
在1955到2000年的研究文獻進行的一項調查顯示，每100個人中至少一個人可能有一些雙性人特徵。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=How sexually dimorphic are we? Review and synthesis|first1=Melanie|last2=Charuvastra|first2=Anthony|date=March 2000|journal=American Journal of Human Biology|issue=2|doi=10.1002/(SICI)1520-6300(200003/04)12:2<151::AID-AJHB1>3.0.CO;2-F|volume=12|pages=151–66|issn=1520-6300|pmid=11534012|last3=Derryck|first3=Amanda|last4=Fausto-Sterling|first4=Anne|last5=Lauzanne|first5=Karl|last6=Lee|first6=Ellen|last1=Blackless|s2cid=453278}}</ref>根據[[聯合國人權事務高級專員辦事處|聯合國人權事務高級專員辦事處]]的說法，人類或其他動物的性別特徵包括[[染色體|染色體]]、性腺、性激素或生殖器的[[變異|變異]]導致「不符合男性或女性身體的典型二元概念」。<ref name="unfe-fact">{{Cite web|title=Free & Equal Campaign Fact Sheet: Intersex|url=https://unfe.org/system/unfe-65-Intersex_Factsheet_ENGLISH.pdf|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|date=2015|publisher=United Nations [[Office_of_the_High_Commissioner_for_Human_Rights|Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights]]|access-date=28 March 2016|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304071043/https://unfe.org/system/unfe-65-Intersex_Factsheet_ENGLISH.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>雙性人的[[變異|變異]]可能使嬰兒時期的[[性別指定|性別指定]]複雜化，<ref name="Mieszczak2009">{{cite journal|title=Assignment of the sex of rearing in the neonate with a disorder of sex development|first1=J|last2=Houk|first2=CP|date=Aug 2009|journal=Curr Opin Pediatr|issue=4|doi=10.1097/mop.0b013e32832c6d2c|volume=21|pages=541–47|pmc=4104182|pmid=19444113|last3=Lee|first3=PA|last1=Mieszczak}}</ref>並且該指定可能與孩子未來的性別認同不一致。<ref name="coe">{{Citation|last1=Council of Europe|title=Human rights and intersex people, Issue Paper|date=April 2015|url=https://wcd.coe.int/ViewDoc.jsp?Ref=CommDH/IssuePaper(2015)1&Language=lanEnglish&Ver=original|last2=Commissioner for Human Rights|author1-link=Council of Europe|accessdate=2021-10-02|archive-date=2016-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160106203349/https://wcd.coe.int/ViewDoc.jsp?Ref=CommDH%2FIssuePaper%282015%291&Language=lanEnglish&Ver=original|dead-url=no}}</ref>人們通常認為通過[[性別指定手術|性別指定手術]]或[[荷爾蒙治療|荷爾蒙治療]]的干預來強化性別指定會侵犯個人的[[人權|人權]]。<ref name="swissnek">{{Cite book|last=Swiss National Advisory Commission on Biomedical Ethics NEK-CNE|url=http://www.nek-cne.ch/fileadmin/nek-cne-dateien/Themen/Stellungnahmen/en/NEK_Intersexualitaet_En.pdf|title=On the management of differences of sex development. Ethical issues relating to "intersexuality".Opinion No. 20/2012|date=November 2012|series=2012|location=Berne|access-date=2016-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150423213245/http://www.nek-cne.ch/fileadmin/nek-cne-dateien/Themen/Stellungnahmen/en/NEK_Intersexualitaet_En.pdf|archive-date=2015-04-23|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="who2015">{{Cite book|last=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]]|title=Sexual health, human rights and the law|date=2015|publisher=World Health Organization|isbn=978-9241564984|location=Geneva}}</ref>

2005年對以女性身份被撫養長大的雙性人，出生時XY染色體、陰莖發育不全、膀胱洩漏性外翻及陰莖外傷，的性別認同研究，結果發現78％的研究對象以女性身份生活，而22％的人決定根據其遺傳染色體為男性而進行性別轉換。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Gender identity outcome in female-raised 46,XY persons with penile agenesis, cloacal exstrophy of the bladder, or penile ablation|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_archives-of-sexual-behavior_2005-08_34_4/page/423|last=Meyer-Bahlburg|first=HF|journal=Archives of Sexual Behavior|issue=4|doi=10.1007/s10508-005-4342-9|year=2005|volume=34|pages=423–38|pmid=16010465}}</ref>这项研究的结论是：「研究結果清楚地表明，在嬰兒或幼儿期性別被指定爲女性後，後來患者決定性別重新指定成男性的幾率增加，但與產前接受雄激素就完全確定核心性別認同的概念不相符。」

一份2012年的临床回顾报告发现，有8.5%至20%的雙性人經歷過[[性別不安|性別不安]]。<ref name="furtado">{{cite journal|title=Gender dysphoria associated with disorders of sex development|author=Furtado P. S.|url=|journal=Nat. Rev. Urol.|issue=11|doi=10.1038/nrurol.2012.182|year=2012|volume=9|pages=620–27|pmid=23045263|display-authors=etal}}</ref>澳大利亞是承認第三性別選項的國家，社會學研究表明，在出生時具有非典型性別特徵的人當中有19％選擇了「X」或「其他」選項，而其他有52％選擇女性，23％選擇男性，6％為不確定。研究中有52％的人在出生時被指定女性，有41％出生時被指定男性。<ref name="oiijones">{{cite web|title=New publication "Intersex: Stories and Statistics from Australia"|url=https://oii.org.au/30313/intersex-stories-statistics-australia/|accessdate=2016-08-18|date=February 3, 2016|website=[[Organisation_Intersex_International_Australia|Organisation Intersex International Australia]]|archive-date=2016-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160829033933/https://oii.org.au/30313/intersex-stories-statistics-australia/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="jones2016">{{Cite book|last1=Jones|last6=Lucke|archivedate=14 September 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914152729/http://oii.org.au/wp-content/uploads/key/Intersex-Stories-Statistics-Australia.pdf|accessdate=2 February 2016|location=Cambridge, UK|isbn=978-1-78374-208-0|publisher=Open Book Publishers|date=2016|first6=Jayne|first5=William|first1=Tiffany|last5=Leonard|first4=Gavi|last4=Ansara|first3=Morgan|last3=Carpenter|first2=Bonnie|last2=Hart|title=Intersex: Stories and Statistics from Australia|url=http://oii.org.au/wp-content/uploads/key/Intersex-Stories-Statistics-Australia.pdf|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==== 跨性別 ====
{{Main|跨性別成因}}
決定性別的激素是在胎兒發育的早期階段產生的。<ref>Lynda Birke, ''In Pursuit Of Difference, scientific studies of women and men'', in ''The Gender and Science Reader'', page 310</ref>如果產前激素的水平發生改變，性[[表型|表型]]的發展也可能發生改變，大腦對一種性別的自然傾向可能與嬰兒外部性器官的遺傳構成不一致。{{citation needed|date=November 2015}}<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Prenatal endocrine influences on sexual orientation and on sexually differentiated childhood behavior|last=Hines|first=Melissa|date=2017-02-02|journal=Frontiers in Neuroendocrinology|issue=2|doi=10.1016/j.yfrne.2011.02.006|volume=32|pages=170–182|issn=0091-3022|pmc=3296090|pmid=21333673}}</ref>

激素可能影響男性和女性的言語和空間能力、記憶力和攻擊性之間的差異。產前激素的暴露影響下視丘調節生命青春期的激素分泌，如女性的性激素通常在月經週期後產生，而男性的性激素不遵循這種模式。<ref>Lynda Birke suggests that during the early stage of fetal development, specific hormones will enter the brain and “permanently affect how the hypothalamus works. As before, high levels of hormones known as androgens will stop the hypothalamus from ever organizing hormone cycles. If there are low levels, then it will be cyclic.” This early influence on brain determines the different frequency of hormone secretion later in male or female’s life. “Obviously, women’s sex hormones usually follow a monthly cycle,” while “men’s sex hormones do not follow such a pattern.” {{cite book|last=Birke|first=Lynda|title=The Gender and Science Reader|pages=313}}</ref>

=== 社會和環境因素 ===
社会科学家倾向于认为性别认同是由社会因素引起的。<ref name="Kiecolt">{{cite book|last1=Kiecolt|editor1-last=Stets|editor2-first=Richard T.|editor2-last=Serpe|ref=harv|chapter=Gender Identity Among U.S. Adults|page=195|editor1-first=Jan E.|isbn=978-0-1908-7306-6|first1=K. Jill|publisher=Oxford University Press|date=2019|first3=Hans|last3=Momsplair|first2=Michael|last2=Hughes|title=Identities in Everyday Life|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iCSQDwAAQBAJ&q=%22rooted+in+social+structure%22|access-date=2020-08-23|archive-date=2021-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203231513/https://books.google.com/books?id=iCSQDwAAQBAJ&q=%22rooted+in+social+structure%22|dead-url=no}}</ref>1955年，約翰·曼尼提出性別認同具有可塑性，並取決於兒童在幼兒時期被當作男性還是女性來撫養。<ref>J. Money, J. G. Hampson, and J. L. Hampson, ''An examination of some basic sexual concepts'', 1955</ref><ref name="GDDSD">A. L. C. de Vries, et al., ''Gender Dysphoria and Disorders of Sex Development'' (2013, {{ISBN|1461474418}})</ref>曼尼的假設從此遭到质疑，<ref name="GDDSD"/><ref>Anne Fausto-Sterling, ''Sexing the Body: Gender Politics and the Construct''</ref>但學者們繼續研究社會因素對性別認同形成的影響。<ref name="GDDSD"/>在1960年至1970年，像是從小父親的缺席、母親對女兒的期望或父母的強化教育方式等因素都会被認為对性别认同的形成产生影响。最近的一些理論認為，父母的[[精神病理學|精神病理]]問題可能会部分影响性別認同的形成，但仅得到了極少的經驗證據。<ref name="GDDSD"/>2004年的一篇文章指出「缺乏對出生後社會因素的重要性確鑿證據」。<ref>D. F. Swaab, ''Sexual differentiation of the human brain: relevance for gender identity, transsexualism and sexual orientation'', in ''Gynecological Endocrinology'', 2004: "...direct effects of testosterone on the developing fetal brain are of major importance for the development of male gender identity and male heterosexual orientation. Solid evidence for the importance of postnatal social factors is lacking."</ref>2008年的一項研究發現，除了母親有輕度[[抑鬱症|抑鬱症]]之外，[[性別不安|性別不安]]兒童的父母沒有表現出任何精神病理問題的跡象。<ref name="GDDSD"/><ref>M. S. C. Wallien, ''Psychosexual outcome of gender-dysphoric children'' (2008)</ref>

有人認為，儘管證據很少，但儿童父母的态度可能会影响儿童的性别认同。<ref>M Weinraub, LP Clemens, A Sockloff, T Ethridge, ''The development of sex role stereotypes in the third year: relationships to gender labeling, gender identity, sex-types toy preference, and family characteristics'', in ''Child Development'', 1984: "Previous investigators have failed to observe a relationship between parental attitudes and children's early sex role acquisition..."</ref>

==非常規性別與跨性別==
{{Main article|非常規性別|跨性別|變性|性別酷兒}}
{{See also|順性別}}
性別認同可能導致不適合二元性別範疇的人士的安全問題。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Gender Identity and the Subject of Security|first1=Gunhild|last2=Rottem|first2=Svein Vigeland|date=2016-06-29|journal=Security Dialogue|issue=2|doi=10.1177/0967010604044974|volume=35|pages=155–71|language=en|last1=Hoogensen|s2cid=55600340}}</ref>在某些情況下，一個人的性別認同與其外顯[[生物性別|生物性別]]特徵（生殖器和[[第二性徵|第二性徵]]）不一致，導致個人穿著或行為的方式被他人視為局外性別文化形式。這些[[性別表現|性別表現]]可以被描述為[[非常規性別|非常規性別]]、[[跨性別|跨性別]]或[[性別酷兒|性別酷兒]]（也就是説明那些違抗傳統性別身份的新興詞彙）。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Atypical Gender Development – A Review|url=http://www.gires.org.uk/genderdev.php|last=Blackless|first=Melanie|journal=International Journal of Transgenderism|accessdate=2008-09-28|doi=10.1300/J485v09n01_04|year=2003|volume=9|pages=29–44|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081007055838/http://www.gires.org.uk/genderdev.php|archivedate=2008-10-07|author3=Carr, S.|author4=Cohen-Kettenis, P.T.|author5=Connolly, P.|author6=De Sutter, P.|author7=Diamond, M.|author8=Di Ceglie, D.|author9=Higashi, Y.|url-status=dead|author17=Reiner, W.G.|author12=Martin, J.|author13=Playdon, Z-J.|author14=Ralph, D.|author16=Reid, R.|author20=Wilson, P.|author18=Swaab, D.|author19=Terry, T.|author2=Besser, M.|author21=Wylie, K.|author10=Jones, L.|author11=Kruijver. F.P.M.|author15=Reed, T.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=27 May 2011|title=Toronto couple defend move to keep baby's sex secret|work=BBC News|publisher=|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-13581835|via=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=2020-08-22|archive-date=2018-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180311210348/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-13581835|dead-url=no}}</ref>並且有這種[[性別表達|性別表現]]的人可能經歷[[性別不安|性別不安]]（傳統上稱為[[性別認同障礙|性別認同障礙]]或GID）。跨性別者在[[性別轉換|性別轉換]]之前，之間和之後往往受到语言和性别代词的极大影响。<ref>{{cite web|title=Words Matter: Affirming Gender Identity Through Language|url=http://www.insightintodiversity.com/words-matter-affirming-gender-identity-through-language/|date=18 May 2016|access-date=2018-08-04|archive-date=2017-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801082447/http://www.insightintodiversity.com/words-matter-affirming-gender-identity-through-language/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

近幾十年來，通過[[性別重置手術|性別重置手術]][[性別指定|重新指定性別]]已成為可能。一些經歷[[性別不安|性別不安]]的人尋求這樣的醫療干預，使他們的[[生理性別|生理性別]]與他們的性別認同相匹配；其他人則保留他們出生時的生殖器（出于某些可能的原因，请参见[[变性|变性]]），但採取與其性別認同一致的[[性別角色|性別角色]]。

